Requirements

Please install the following packages which are required for static and dynamic mapping:

install.packages("leaflet")
install.packages("rgdal")
install.packages("raster")

and then invoke them:

Basics: Tiles

"A tile map (raster or vector) is a map displayed in a browser by seamlessly joining dozens of individually requested image files over the internet."

Let's create a simple map:

library(leaflet)   # load the library
mymap<-leaflet() %>%
  addTiles # images you are going to see
mymap   #check the map

Now, it is time to explore different tiles! CartoDB:

mymap<-leaflet() %>%
  addProviderTiles(provider ="CartoDB.Positron")
mymap   #check the map

ESRI World Imagery:

mymap<-leaflet() %>%
  addProviderTiles(provider ="Esri.WorldImagery")
mymap   #check the map

What about night lights:

mymap<-leaflet() %>%
  addProviderTiles(provider ="NASAGIBS.ViirsEarthAtNight2012")
mymap   #check the map

Now that we have the basic map, let's populate it with some fun data!

Project 1: Load data points

Download the datasets available in canopy (MOCK_DATA.csv):

data<-read.csv("MOCK_DATA.csv")

mymap<-leaflet(data = data) %>%
  addTiles %>% # images you are going to see
  addMarkers(lng = ~long,
             lat = ~lat,
             popup = ~city)
mymap   #check the map

  • Remember these dataset have no real data, it was created for learning purposes.

Project 2: Processing your data

data<-read.csv("MOCK_DATA2.csv")

mymap<-leaflet(data=data) %>%
  addTiles %>% # images you are going to see
  addMarkers(lng = ~long,
             lat = ~lat,
             popup = ~country)
mymap   #check the map

onlyUS<-data[data$country=="US",]
cleanUS<-na.omit(onlyUS)
mymap<-leaflet(data = cleanUS) %>%
  addTiles %>% # images you are going to see
  addMarkers(lng = ~long,
             lat = ~lat,
             popup = ~income)
mymap   #check the map

Project 4: Depicts US Annual temperature

Our objetive is to depict the US climate using static and interactive visualization. We can get the raster data or human generated images that measure these values (precipitation, population density, etc) from:

  • World Climate Data (Tmin, Tmax, Precip, BioClim)
  • GADM Global adm. boundaries (different levels)

# get climate data
climate <- getData ('worldclim', var='bio', res=10) 
plot(climate$bio1)

par( mfrow=c(1,2) )
# Country level boundaries of US
myRaster <- getData('GADM', country='USA', level=0)
plot(myRaster)
# crop the us climate data
clippedRaster <- mask(climate$bio1, myRaster)
plot(clippedRaster)

Create the interactive version of it:

# Show clipped raster
pal <- colorNumeric(c("#0C2C84", "#41B6C4", "#FFFFCC"), 
                    values(clippedRaster),
                    na.color = "transparent")
map_leaflet <- leaflet() %>%
  addTiles() %>%
  addRasterImage(clippedRaster, colors = pal, opacity = 0.8)  %>%
  addLegend(pal = pal, values = values(clippedRaster), 
            title = "Anual Mean Temperature Values in US") 
map_leaflet
